# 🔹 LAYER 1 – Eligibility Filter (Deterministic Engine)

## Type
Rule-based backend logic with **versioned rule sets**

## Input
- Student profile (branch, CGPA, batch, backlog count, gap years)
- Job eligibility criteria (set by HR per job posting)

## Output

| Status | Description |
|---|---|
| `ELIGIBLE` | Meets all criteria |
| `BORDERLINE_ELIGIBLE` | Within 5% margin of one criterion (e.g., CGPA 6.9 when cutoff is 7.0) — flagged for HR review |
| `INELIGIBLE` | Does not meet criteria — hard reject with reason logged |

## Eligibility Criteria (Expanded)

| Criterion | Type | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Branch | Exact match / list | CSE, IT, ECE |
| Minimum CGPA | Numeric threshold | ≥ 7.0 |
| Batch year | Exact / range | 2025, 2026 |
| Active backlogs | Count threshold | 0 allowed |
| Backlog history | Count threshold | ≤ 2 historical |
| Gap year policy | Boolean / count | ≤ 1 year gap allowed |
| Lateral entry | Boolean | Allowed / Not allowed |

## Rule Versioning

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Every time HR modifies eligibility criteria, the system **snapshots the rule set** and associates it with the job posting. This ensures full auditability.

```
eligibility_rule_versions table:
┌──────────┬────────────┬──────────────┬────────────────────┬────────────┐
│ rule_id  │ job_id     │ rule_json    │ created_at         │ created_by │
├──────────┼────────────┼──────────────┼────────────────────┼────────────┤
│ R001     │ JOB-2025-1 │ {cgpa: 7.0…} │ 2025-01-15 10:00  │ HR_Admin   │
│ R002     │ JOB-2025-1 │ {cgpa: 6.5…} │ 2025-01-20 14:30  │ HR_Admin   │
└──────────┴────────────┴──────────────┴────────────────────┴────────────┘
```

## Why Rule-Based
- Campus hiring requires **strict compliance** — no probabilistic decisions
- Full auditability — every rejection has a documented reason
- No bias introduction — same rules applied to every candidate
- Legally defensible — can justify every decision with rule + data

## Why NOT ML
- Non-deterministic — cannot guarantee same decision for same input
- Legally risky — cannot explain rejection to a candidate
- Hard to justify — "the model said so" is not acceptable in campus placement

