# 🔹 LAYER 3 – Skill Intelligence Layer (Revised)

## Technology
**Hierarchical Skill Taxonomy** stored in JSON / Database with admin UI

## Purpose
- Normalize skill names (synonyms, abbreviations, variations)
- Map related technologies into hierarchical categories
- Avoid duplication in scoring
- Enable **partial credit** matching via hierarchy
- Track skill proficiency levels when available

## Hierarchical Skill Taxonomy (NEW)

```
Technology Skills
├── Programming Languages
│   ├── Python
│   │   ├── aliases: ["python3", "py"]
│   │   └── proficiency_detectable: true
│   ├── JavaScript
│   │   ├── aliases: ["JS", "js", "Javascript"]
│   │   └── children:
│   │       ├── React.js → aliases: ["React", "ReactJS"]
│   │       ├── Node.js → aliases: ["Node", "NodeJS"]
│   │       ├── Angular → aliases: ["AngularJS", "Angular2+"]
│   │       ├── Vue.js → aliases: ["Vue", "VueJS"]
│   │       └── Express.js → aliases: ["Express"]
│   ├── Java
│   │   └── children:
│   │       ├── Spring Boot → aliases: ["SpringBoot", "Spring"]
│   │       └── Hibernate
│   ├── C++
│   │   └── aliases: ["cpp", "C Plus Plus"]
│   └── C#
│       └── aliases: ["C Sharp", "CSharp"]
│
├── Databases
│   ├── SQL
│   │   ├── MySQL → aliases: ["mysql", "My SQL"]
│   │   ├── PostgreSQL → aliases: ["Postgres", "psql", "PG"]
│   │   └── SQLite
│   └── NoSQL
│       ├── MongoDB → aliases: ["Mongo"]
│       ├── Redis
│       ├── Cassandra
│       └── Firebase → aliases: ["Firebase Realtime DB"]
│
├── Cloud & DevOps
│   ├── AWS → aliases: ["Amazon Web Services"]
│   │   ├── EC2
│   │   ├── S3
│   │   ├── Lambda
│   │   └── RDS
│   ├── Docker → aliases: ["docker", "containerization"]
│   ├── Kubernetes → aliases: ["K8s", "k8s"]
│   ├── Git → aliases: ["GitHub", "GitLab", "Version Control"]
│   └── CI/CD → aliases: ["Jenkins", "GitHub Actions"]
│
├── ML / AI
│   ├── Machine Learning → aliases: ["ML", "ml"]
│   ├── Deep Learning → aliases: ["DL", "dl"]
│   ├── TensorFlow → aliases: ["TF", "tf"]
│   ├── PyTorch → aliases: ["pytorch"]
│   ├── scikit-learn → aliases: ["sklearn", "Scikit Learn"]
│   ├── NLP → aliases: ["Natural Language Processing"]
│   ├── Computer Vision → aliases: ["CV", "Image Processing"]
│   └── OpenCV
│
├── Web Frameworks
│   ├── Backend
│   │   ├── FastAPI
│   │   ├── Django
│   │   ├── Flask
│   │   └── Spring Boot (→ linked to Java)
│   └── Frontend
│       ├── React.js (→ linked to JavaScript)
│       ├── Angular (→ linked to JavaScript)
│       └── HTML/CSS → aliases: ["HTML5", "CSS3"]
│
└── Data & Analytics
    ├── Pandas → aliases: ["pandas"]
    ├── NumPy → aliases: ["numpy"]
    ├── Tableau
    ├── Power BI → aliases: ["PowerBI"]
    └── Excel → aliases: ["MS Excel", "Advanced Excel"]
```

## Synonym & Abbreviation Mapping (NEW)

| Raw Text (from resume) | Normalized Skill |
|---|---|
| JS | JavaScript |
| ML | Machine Learning |
| DL | Deep Learning |
| K8s | Kubernetes |
| Postgres | PostgreSQL |
| py | Python |
| sklearn | scikit-learn |
| React | React.js |
| Node | Node.js |
| Mongo | MongoDB |
| AWS EC2 | AWS → EC2 |
| tf | TensorFlow |
| cpp | C++ |

## Skill Proficiency Levels (NEW)

When resumes contain proficiency indicators, capture them:

| Level | Keywords Detected |
|---|---|
| **Expert** | "expert", "mastery", "advanced proficiency" |
| **Advanced** | "advanced", "proficient", "strong" |
| **Intermediate** | "intermediate", "working knowledge", "familiar" |
| **Beginner** | "beginner", "basic", "exposure", "learning" |
| **Unspecified** | No indicator found (default) |

## Partial Credit via Hierarchy (NEW)

When a JD requires a skill and the candidate has a **related** skill:

| JD Requirement | Candidate Has | Credit |
|---|---|---|
| "React.js" | "React.js" | 100% (exact match) |
| "JavaScript Framework" | "React.js" | 90% (child of JS → Framework) |
| "JavaScript" | "React.js" | 70% (parent skill known) |
| "Frontend Development" | "React.js" | 50% (category match) |
| "Web Development" | "React.js" | 30% (broad category) |
| "Python" | "React.js" | 0% (unrelated) |

## Taxonomy Versioning (NEW)

```
taxonomy_versions table:
┌──────────┬────────────────┬────────────────────┬────────────┐
│ version  │ changes_json   │ effective_date     │ updated_by │
├──────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────┼────────────┤
│ v1.0     │ {initial}      │ 2025-01-01         │ system     │
│ v1.1     │ {+Rust, +Go}   │ 2025-03-15         │ HR_Admin   │
│ v1.2     │ {+LangChain}   │ 2025-06-01         │ HR_Admin   │
└──────────┴────────────────┴────────────────────┴────────────┘
```

## Admin UI for Taxonomy Management (NEW)

- HR can add/edit/delete skills without code changes
- Drag-and-drop hierarchy management
- Bulk import from CSV
- Change log for audit trail

## Why NOT ML Here?

- Skill normalization is a **deterministic ontology problem**
- Business must **control** what counts as a valid skill
- No need for probabilistic guessing — either "React" = "React.js" or it doesn't
- Taxonomy updates must be **instant and auditable**

