# 🔹 LAYER 4 – Semantic Matching Layer (Revised)

## Model Used
**Sentence-BERT** (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`)

## Architecture: Section-Level Embedding (NEW)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Do NOT embed the entire resume as one blob.** Embed structured sections separately for dramatically better matching accuracy.

### Resume Embedding Strategy

```
Resume Structured Data
    │
    ├── skills_text = "Python, React.js, PostgreSQL, Docker, TensorFlow..."
    │   └── skills_embedding = SBERT.encode(skills_text)         → 384-dim vector
    │
    ├── projects_text = "E-Commerce Recommendation Engine using collaborative filtering..."
    │   └── projects_embedding = SBERT.encode(projects_text)     → 384-dim vector
    │
    ├── experience_text = "Software Development Intern at Infosys, built REST APIs..."
    │   └── experience_embedding = SBERT.encode(experience_text) → 384-dim vector
    │
    └── overall_embedding = weighted_average(
            skills_embedding × 0.35,
            projects_embedding × 0.40,
            experience_embedding × 0.25
        )                                                        → 384-dim vector
```

### JD Embedding Strategy

```
Job Description
    │
    ├── required_skills_text = "Python, Machine Learning, SQL, Cloud deployment..."
    │   └── jd_skills_embedding = SBERT.encode(required_skills_text)
    │
    ├── role_description_text = "Build ML pipelines for production recommendation systems..."
    │   └── jd_role_embedding = SBERT.encode(role_description_text)
    │
    └── jd_overall_embedding = weighted_average(
            jd_skills_embedding × 0.40,
            jd_role_embedding × 0.60
        )
```

### Similarity Computation

```
Section-Level Cosine Similarity:
    skill_similarity      = cosine(resume.skills_emb, jd.skills_emb)
    project_similarity    = cosine(resume.projects_emb, jd.role_emb)
    experience_similarity = cosine(resume.experience_emb, jd.role_emb)

Global Similarity:
    global_similarity     = cosine(resume.overall_emb, jd.overall_emb)

All four scores are passed to Layer 5 (Scoring Engine)
```

## JD Embedding Cache (NEW)

- JDs don't change after posting → compute embedding **once**, store in Redis/DB
- Only compute resume embeddings at upload time
- Saves ~50% compute per matching operation

```
jd_embeddings_cache table:
┌──────────┬─────────────────┬──────────────────────────┬────────────────────┐
│ job_id   │ embedding_type  │ embedding_vector (384d)  │ computed_at        │
├──────────┼─────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼────────────────────┤
│ JOB-001  │ skills          │ [0.023, -0.114, ...]     │ 2025-01-15 10:00   │
│ JOB-001  │ role            │ [0.045, 0.089, ...]      │ 2025-01-15 10:00   │
│ JOB-001  │ overall         │ [0.034, -0.012, ...]     │ 2025-01-15 10:00   │
└──────────┴─────────────────┴──────────────────────────┴────────────────────┘
```

## Similarity Threshold Filtering (NEW)

| Global Cosine Similarity | Action |
|---|---|
| ≥ 0.60 | Strong match — proceed to scoring |
| 0.30 – 0.59 | Moderate match — score but flag |
| < 0.30 | Weak match — flag as "Likely Irrelevant" for HR review |

This prevents a CS student's resume from scoring highly on a Mechanical Engineering JD.

## Why Sentence-BERT (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`)?

| Advantage | Detail |
|---|---|
| Designed for similarity | Purpose-built for semantic textual similarity |
| Lightweight | ~22M parameters |
| Fast inference | <50ms per encoding on CPU |
| CPU-friendly | No GPU required |
| Fine-tunable | Can be fine-tuned on domain-specific data later (Layer 6) |
| No API cost | Self-hosted, open-source |
| Deterministic | Same input → same output every time |

## Why NOT Alternatives?

| Model | Reason Rejected |
|---|---|
| TF-IDF | Keyword-based — misses semantic relationships |
| Word2Vec | No sentence-level context |
| BERT embeddings (CLS) | Heavy, not optimized for similarity |
| GPT embeddings | API cost, vendor dependency |
| Cross-Encoder | Slow inference — compares pairs, doesn't scale |
| **Sentence-BERT** | **✅ Best similarity efficiency** |

---

---

# 🔹 LAYER 5 – Evidence-Based Scoring Engine (Revised & Improved)

## Type
**Deterministic 6-dimension weighted scoring** with per-job-type configurable weights and detailed rubrics

## Why Deterministic?
- **Transparent** — every score can be explained
- **Adjustable** — HR can tune weights per role type
- **Auditable** — full scoring breakdown available
- **HR-trust aligned** — no "black box" decisions

## Scoring Dimensions (Revised — 6 Dimensions)

| # | Dimension | Default Weight | Source Layer |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Skill Coverage | 20% | Layer 3 (Taxonomy Match) |
| 2 | Project Relevance & Complexity | 25% | Layer 2 (NER) + Layer 4 (Similarity) |
| 3 | Internship/Experience Relevance | 15% | Layer 2 (NER) + Layer 4 (Similarity) |
| 4 | Education Quality | 15% | Layer 1 (Profile) + Layer 2 (NER) |
| 5 | Global Semantic Alignment | 10% | Layer 4 (Overall Similarity) |
| 6 | Authenticity & Consistency | 15% | Cross-section analysis |

### Total: 100%

---

### Dimension 1: Skill Coverage (20%)

```
skill_score = (matched_skills / required_skills) × 100

With partial credit:
    exact_match    = 1.0 × weight
    child_match    = 0.9 × weight  (React.js matches "JS Framework")
    parent_match   = 0.7 × weight  (JavaScript matches "React.js")
    category_match = 0.5 × weight  (Frontend Dev matches "React.js")
```

| Metric | Scoring |
|---|---|
| 100% skills matched | 10/10 |
| 80–99% matched | 8/10 |
| 60–79% matched | 6/10 |
| 40–59% matched | 4/10 |
| < 40% matched | 2/10 |

---

### Dimension 2: Project Relevance & Complexity (25%)

**Relevance** = cosine similarity between project descriptions and JD role description (from Layer 4)

**Complexity Rubric (NEW):**

| Signal | Points |
|---|---|
| Uses 3+ technologies | +2 |
| Has deployment (live URL mentioned) | +3 |
| Has GitHub / source link | +2 |
| Team project (mentions "team", "collaborated") | +1 |
| Duration > 2 months | +1 |
| ML/AI/Cloud component | +2 |
| Real-world application (vs academic exercise) | +1 |
| Solo project with full-stack scope | +2 |
| Hackathon / competition project | +1 |

**Scoring:**

| Combined Score | Rating |
|---|---|
| ≥ 12 points | 10/10 |
| 9–11 points | 8/10 |
| 6–8 points | 6/10 |
| 3–5 points | 4/10 |
| < 3 points | 2/10 |

---

### Dimension 3: Internship/Experience Relevance (15%)

| Signal | Points |
|---|---|
| Internship at recognized company | +3 |
| Role aligns with JD | +3 (via cosine similarity) |
| Duration ≥ 3 months | +2 |
| Duration ≥ 6 months | +3 |
| Technologies used overlap with JD | +2 |
| Multiple internships | +1 per additional |
| No internship found | 2/10 base score |

---

### Dimension 4: Education Quality (15%) — NEW

| Signal | Points |
|---|---|
| CGPA ≥ 9.0 | +4 |
| CGPA 8.0–8.9 | +3 |
| CGPA 7.0–7.9 | +2 |
| CGPA 6.0–6.9 | +1 |
| Tier-1 institution (IIT/NIT/IIIT/BITS) | +3 |
| Tier-2 institution (state colleges, reputed private) | +2 |
| Other | +1 |
| Relevant major (CSE for CS role) | +2 |
| Partially relevant major (ECE for CS role) | +1 |
| Relevant coursework mentioned | +1 |

---

### Dimension 5: Global Semantic Alignment (10%)

Direct output from Layer 4:

```
semantic_score = cosine_similarity(resume_overall_embedding, jd_overall_embedding) × 10
```

| Cosine Similarity | Score |
|---|---|
| ≥ 0.80 | 10/10 |
| 0.60 – 0.79 | 7/10 |
| 0.40 – 0.59 | 5/10 |
| 0.20 – 0.39 | 3/10 |
| < 0.20 | 1/10 |

---

### Dimension 6: Authenticity & Consistency (15%) — Concrete Metrics (NEW)

| Check | Detection Method | Points Deducted |
|---|---|---|
| **Date inconsistency** | Overlapping internship + academic dates | -3 |
| **Skill-project mismatch** | Claims Python skill but no project uses Python | -2 per mismatch |
| **CGPA-achievement gap** | CGPA < 7.0 but claims "top performer" | -1 (flag for review) |
| **Inflated content** | Resume > 2 pages for a fresher | -1 |
| **Buzzword stuffing** | >15 skills listed with no project evidence | -2 |
| **Consistent timeline** | Education → Internships → Projects flow logically | +2 |
| **Evidence-backed claims** | Skills appear in project descriptions | +3 |
| **Verifiable links** | GitHub, LinkedIn, portfolio present | +2 |

**Base score: 7/10. Adjustments applied from table above. Clamped to [0, 10].**

---

## Per-Job-Type Weight Profiles (NEW)

| Role Type | Skill | Project | Internship | Education | Semantic | Authenticity |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| **Software Engineer** | 20% | 25% | 15% | 15% | 10% | 15% |
| **Data Scientist / ML** | 25% | 30% | 10% | 15% | 10% | 10% |
| **Web Developer** | 25% | 30% | 10% | 10% | 10% | 15% |
| **Management Trainee** | 10% | 15% | 25% | 20% | 15% | 15% |
| **Research Intern** | 15% | 30% | 10% | 25% | 10% | 10% |
| **Custom** | HR defined | HR defined | HR defined | HR defined | HR defined | HR defined |

---

## Final Score Calculation

```
FINAL_SCORE = (
    skill_score       × skill_weight +
    project_score     × project_weight +
    internship_score  × internship_weight +
    education_score   × education_weight +
    semantic_score    × semantic_weight +
    authenticity_score × authenticity_weight
) / 10 × 100

Result: Score out of 100
```

---

