# 🔹 LAYER 6 – Feedback & Calibration Layer (Revised)

## Stores (Outcome Tracking)

| Outcome Stage | Data Captured |
|---|---|
| **Applied** | Resume uploaded, parsed, scored |
| **Shortlisted** | Score-based shortlist + HR override decisions |
| **Interviewed** | Interview feedback (structured) |
| **Selected** | Final offer extended |
| **Rejected** | Stage of rejection + reason |

## Feedback Loop: Concrete Implementation (NEW)

```
FEEDBACK CALIBRATION PIPELINE:

Step 1: After hiring round completes
    → HR marks final outcomes (Selected / Rejected per stage)

Step 2: System runs correlation analysis
    → For SELECTED candidates:
        What was their average score per dimension?
        What dimensions had highest/lowest variance?
    → For REJECTED candidates:
        Did high-scoring candidates get rejected? (false positives)
        Did low-scoring candidates get selected? (false negatives)

Step 3: Generate weight adjustment suggestions
    → If project_relevance had low correlation with selection:
        Suggest reducing project weight by 5%
    → If internship_relevance had high correlation with selection:
        Suggest increasing internship weight by 5%

Step 4: HR reviews and approves/rejects adjustments
    → No automatic weight changes — HR controls the system

Step 5: If approved, new weight profile is versioned and stored
    → Old weights retained for comparison

Step 6: System scores next batch with new weights
```

## A/B Testing for Weights (NEW)

When testing new weight configurations:

```
Candidate Pool
    │
    ├── Score with Weight Profile A (current production weights)
    │   └── Rank list A
    │
    └── Score with Weight Profile B (proposed new weights)
        └── Rank list B

Compare:
    • How many candidates change rank significantly?
    • Do known-good candidates rank higher with B?
    • Does B reduce false positives from historical data?

HR reviews comparison → Approves or rejects switch to Profile B
```

## Parsing Accuracy Metrics (NEW)

Track and display:

| Metric | Target | Description |
|---|---|---|
| Parse success rate | ≥ 95% | % of resumes with status `PARSED` |
| NER F1 score | ≥ 0.85 | Spot-checked against manual labels |
| Skill extraction recall | ≥ 0.90 | % of actual skills captured |
| Section detection accuracy | ≥ 0.92 | % of sections correctly identified |
| OCR fallback rate | < 5% | % of resumes requiring OCR |

## Future: Supervised Ranking Transition Path

```
Phase 1 (Current): Deterministic scoring with fixed weights
Phase 2 (After ~5,000 labeled outcomes): Train logistic regression on outcomes
Phase 3 (After ~20,000 outcomes): Fine-tune Sentence-BERT on domain data
Phase 4 (After ~50,000 outcomes): LambdaMART / Learning-to-Rank model
```

> [!NOTE]
> Each phase transition requires HR approval and A/B testing. The system should never transition to ML-based ranking without sufficient data AND explicit approval.

